.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-PING" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-ping \- send a BOLT-1 ping to a connected peer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-ping
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sends a BOLT-1
.B ping
message to the connected peer identified by
.I peer_id
and reports the total response length.
The peer must currently be connected.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable or the peer is not found.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"totlen":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-info (1),
.BR lightning-node-reachability (1)
